This file defines the main layout for the dashboard section of the application.

**Purpose:**

The `DashboardLayout` component provides a consistent structure for all pages within the `/dashboard` route. It includes a sidebar and a main content area, ensuring a unified user experience.

**Key Exports/Functions/Props:**

*   **`DashboardLayout`**: A React functional component that takes `children` as a prop.
    *   `children`: `React.ReactNode` - The content that will be rendered within the main area of the layout.

**Usage Example:**

This component is automatically applied to any page within the `app/dashboard` directory in a Next.js application. For instance, `app/dashboard/page.tsx` would be rendered inside the `children` prop of this layout.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to your Dashboard!</h1>
      {/* Dashboard content goes here */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

When a user navigates to `/dashboard`, the `DashboardLayout` will render, and the content of `DashboardPage` will be placed within the `<main>` element.
